         The theft unfolded just 250 meters (270 yards) from  the Mona Lisa , in what Culture Minister Rachida Dati described as a professional “four-minute operation.”  One object, the emerald-set imperial crown of Napoleon III’s wife, Empress Eugénie, containing more than 1,300 diamonds, was later found outside the museum, French authorities said. It was reportedly recovered broken. Images from the scene showed confused tourists being steered out of the glass pyramid and adjoining courtyards as officers closed nearby streets along the Seine.  

























